              "text": "Let the second field be 120 tons.\n\n- First field: 2.5 times the second = 2.5 × 120 = 300 tons.\n- Third field: 40% less than the first → 60% of the first = 0.6 × 300 = 180 tons.\n\nTotal production = 120 + 300 + 180 = 600 tons.\n\nAnswer: 600 tons.",
